      <section eId="sec_CCP-3396-11">
        <num>CCP 3396.11</num>
        <heading>3396.11. Â Possibility of renunciation</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3396-11__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The subsequent renunciation of an heir or legatee who has consented to an independent administration shall have no effect on the validity of the independent administration, and the consent of those persons who receive an interest in the succession by reason of the renunciation is not required.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3396-11__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A successor who concurs in the application for independent administration of an estate shall not be considered, for that reason, as having formally or informally accepted the succession.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111742</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
